---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Quickstart — RCAN Robot Communication Protocol";
const description = "From zero to your first RCAN message in 5 minutes.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <div class="mb-8">
      <span class="text-xs font-mono text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-widest">Documentation</span>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-2">Quickstart</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mt-2">From zero to your first RCAN message in 5 minutes.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Step 1 -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">
        <span class="text-blue-400 font-mono mr-2">01</span>Install the SDK
      </h2>
      <pre class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-green-300"><code>pip install rcan

# Optional extras
pip install rcan[http]    # registry client (httpx)
pip install rcan[crypto]  # message signing (Ed25519)
pip install rcan[all]     # everything</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- Step 2 -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">
        <span class="text-blue-400 font-mono mr-2">02</span>Build a Robot URI
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-3">
        Every robot has a globally unique, resolvable address. No more "which unit was it exactly?"
      </p>
      <pre class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-green-300"><code>from rcan import RobotURI

uri = RobotURI.build(
    manufacturer="acme",
    model="robotarm",
    version="v2",
    device_id="unit-001",
)
print(uri)
# rcan://registry.rcan.dev/acme/robotarm/v2/unit-001

# Or parse from a string
uri = RobotURI.parse("rcan://registry.rcan.dev/acme/robotarm/v2/unit-001")
print(uri.namespace)   # acme/robotarm
print(uri.registry_url)  # https://registry.rcan.dev/registry/acme/...</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- Step 3 -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">
        <span class="text-blue-400 font-mono mr-2">03</span>Gate on AI Confidence
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-3">
        The gate doesn't trust the model — that's the point. The model is right 99.99% of the time.
        The gate is for the 0.01%.
      </p>
      <pre class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-green-300"><code>from rcan import RCANMessage, ConfidenceGate

gate = ConfidenceGate(threshold=0.8)
confidence = 0.91  # from your AI model

if gate.allows(confidence):
    msg = RCANMessage(
        cmd="move_forward",
        target=uri,
        params={"distance_m": 1.0},
        confidence=confidence,
        model_identity="Qwen2.5-7B-Q4",
    )
    print(msg.to_json(indent=2))
else:
    print(f"Blocked: confidence {confidence} < threshold {gate.threshold}")</code></pre>

      <p class="text-gray-500 text-xs mt-3">
        For high-stakes actions, add a <code class="text-blue-300">HiTLGate</code> to require explicit human approval.
        See <a href="/spec#section-16" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">§16 AI Accountability</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Step 4 -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">
        <span class="text-blue-400 font-mono mr-2">04</span>Create a Tamper-Evident Audit Record
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-3">
        Every safety-critical action can be sealed into a <code class="text-blue-300">CommitmentRecord</code> — 
        an HMAC-chained record that provides forensic-grade proof of what the system did, when, at what confidence.
      </p>
      <pre class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-green-300"><code>from rcan import CommitmentRecord
from rcan.audit import AuditChain

chain = AuditChain(secret="your-hmac-secret")

record = chain.append(CommitmentRecord(
    action="move_forward",
    robot_uri=str(uri),
    confidence=0.91,
    model_identity="Qwen2.5-7B-Q4",
    params={"distance_m": 1.0},
    safety_approved=True,
))

print(f"Commitment: {record.content_hash}")
print(f"Chain valid: {chain.verify_all()}")  # True

# Export as JSONL for long-term storage
with open("audit.jsonl", "w") as f:
    f.write(chain.to_jsonl())</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- Step 5 -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">
        <span class="text-blue-400 font-mono mr-2">05</span>Register Your Robot
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-3">
        Get a globally unique RRN (Robot Registry Number) for your robot. Free.
      </p>
      <pre class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-green-300"><code># If using OpenCastor — registration is built into the wizard
castor wizard
# → Step 13: Register with rcan.dev? [Y/n]
# → ✅ Robot registered: RRN-00000042

# Or register standalone
castor register --config myrobot.rcan.yaml

# Or via the rcan-py SDK (requires API key from rcan.dev/register)
from rcan.registry import RegistryClient

async with RegistryClient(api_key="rcan_...") as client:
    result = await client.register(
        manufacturer="acme", model="robotarm",
        version="v2", device_id="unit-001",
    )
    print(result["rrn"])  # RRN-00000042</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- Step 6 -->
    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3">
        <span class="text-blue-400 font-mono mr-2">06</span>Validate Your Config
      </h2>
      <pre class="bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-green-300"><code># Validate a RCAN message
rcan-validate message command.json

# Check config conformance (L1/L2/L3)
rcan-validate config myrobot.rcan.yaml

# Or with OpenCastor
castor compliance --config myrobot.rcan.yaml

# Output:
# ✅ L1 — Addressing + message format: passed
# ✅ L2 — Auth + confidence gates: passed
# ⚠️  L3 — hitl_gates not configured
# Result: L2 (1 warning)</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- What's next -->
    <section class="border-t border-gray-800 pt-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">What's next</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        {[
          { href: "/spec", label: "Protocol Spec", desc: "Full RCAN v1.2 specification" },
          { href: "/registry", label: "Robot Registry", desc: "Browse registered robots" },
          { href: "https://github.com/continuonai/rcan-py", label: "rcan-py on GitHub", desc: "Source, issues, PRs" },
          { href: "https://github.com/craigm26/OpenCastor", label: "OpenCastor", desc: "Robot runtime with RCAN built in" },
        ].map(({ href, label, desc }) => (
          <a href={href} class="block p-4 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg hover:border-blue-500 transition-colors">
            <div class="text-white font-medium">{label}</div>
            <div class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-1">{desc}</div>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</Layout>
